That's correct.The way WSL works is that esources are all shared globally across all WSL distributions (podman machine instances + any other WSL instance [e.g. stock Ubuntu instance]). This is mentioned in the man pages for podman machine set for example, that the settings are only relevant for Qemu backed machines, where they are per machine.

If you wish to restrict resources, the way to do that is a user specific `.wslconfig` file:[
](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/wsl/wsl-config)
